text: Didonne Castle () is a castle in the town of Semussac, France. Didonne Castle was built in the first half of the 18th century. It was the home of Marquis Jean Charles de Saint-Nectaire until 1771. He became a Marshal of France in 1757. In 2019, the castle was renovated and turned into a small hotel with ten rooms and a restaurant. == References == Category:Castles in France Category:18th-century buildings and structures
